O_p(1)
X_n = O_p(1)
Y_n = O_p(1)
\epsilon > 0
M
\sup_n P(|X_n| > M) < \epsilon/2
\sup_n  P(|Y_n| > M) < \epsilon/2
\sup_n P(|X_n + Y_n| > M) < \epsilon
P(|X_n + Y_n| > M) \le P(|X_n|+|Y_n| > M)
\{|X_n| + | Y_n| > M \} \subset \{ |X_n| \ge M/2 \} \cup \{|Y_n| \ge M/2 \}
|X_n| + | Y_n| 
M
P(|X_n| + | Y_n| > M ) \le P(|X_n| \ge M/2) + P(|Y_n| \ge M/2)
